Durban - Two men accused of gunning down the chairperson of the African National Congress Youth League in Durban at the weekend, are due in the uMlazi Magistrate's Court on Monday. 
 

 On Saturday, Bongani Usher Mkhize, 25, was shot dead in Yose Drive, V Section. Police said the 29-year old suspected shooter handed himself over to police shortly after the murder. A short while later, another 24-year-old man was arrested by police. 
AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
  

 Police spokesperson, 
 Brigadier Jay Naicker,
  said police also recovered a firearm.

 

 "Charges of murder an unlawful possession of a firearm cases were opened at the uMlazi police station following the shooting. The victim sustained injuries to the body and was declared dead at the scene. The firearm that was used in the commission of the crime was also confiscated from the suspect. The motive for the shooting in unknown at this stage. Both are due in the uMlazi Magistrate's Court," he said. 

 

 The shooting took place on the third and final day of the ANC's provincial conference, which was hosted in Durban. 

 

 Commenting on the murder at the time, #KZNANC newly elected provincial chairperson, Sihle Zikalala, welcomed the arrests. 

 

 Mkhize was described as a "very dedicated and promising young leader". 

 

 ANCYL provincial secretary, Thanduxolo Sabelo, said while the motive of the murder is yet to be established, the league was not ruling out the possibility that it could be politically motivated. 

 

 Mkhize led the league's biggest branch in KZN and was the deputy chairperson of the ANC in Ward 88. He was not a delegate of the ANC provincial conference. 

 

